SIMPLE: facies
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Facies
<hw>Fa"ci*es</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., from, face.
See <er>Face</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The anterior part of the head; the face.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>The general aspect or habit of a
species, or group of species, esp. with reference to its adaptation to
its environment.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The face of a bird, or the front
of the head, excluding the bill.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Facies Hippocratica</b></col>. <fld>(Med.)</fld> <cd>See
<er>Hippocratic</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Facile</ent>⟦br⟧
